result.adr_address: 348 Nathan Rd, Yau Ma Tei, Hong Kong
result.formatted_address: 348 Nathan Rd, Yau Ma Tei, Hong Kong
result.name: The Square Restaurant

reviews.text: A good value for money although choices are limited for lunch. Good quality in general. Some dishes could be made better such as pork steak and shrimp. Definitely, you can find something you like. Excellent service with a clean and decent environment. Would recommend it with a limited budget.

First time trying this restaurant and it will be the last time.  I would give minus one star for the experience.  Had to call three times to make the reservation.  When arrived at the restaurant .. hostess at front shown no interest greeting us.  No server check back on our table during the entire dining, dirty plates weren’t taken away.  
We had the breakfast buffets .. it was a total disappointment.  Not to mention about the little varieties of food, they taste bad.  
The only one thing we appreciated was the chef cooking at the hot counter.  He has shown passionate in serving the guests.
When we pay the bills, we over heard the staffs complainting how tired they are.

The price of the buffet justifies the selection and service you receive here.  There's hot food, salad, sushi & sashimi, dessert and fruit, with ice-cream. If you are looking for a decent basic selection, love a bargain, and don't mind the limited service here, then this is a good choice. The seating is quite good, so there's no long waits.
Food choices is so. Limited during lunch time, its just the shrimp and the haagen dazs ice cream is the main attraction. Service is good though.
A very nice buffet restaurant with an array of food. Häagen-Dazs soft cream is also available for any dessert lovers

result.adr_address: 348 Nathan Rd, Yau Ma Tei, Hong Kong
result.formatted_address: 348 Nathan Rd, Yau Ma Tei, Hong Kong
result.name: Novotel Hong Kong Nathan Road Kowloon

reviews.text:
If you could, book the executive floor. We booked the Deluxe King Room, it was disappointing. Dust was everywhere, disgusting smell, the wall was peeling off and it felt like a motel. I reflected my disappointment on the Novotel survey which was emailed to me after check in. The manager called me and put us on the executive floor instead. It was so much better. For me, the horrific drain smell from the original room being gone was so worth any trouble. 

Front office staff speak good English. A warning, do not purchase their fresh juice from the bar. It’s from a plastic bottle, tastes off. But they do have fresh juices watermelon juice. It was sold out when I wanted to try.

I’m a Le Club Gold member and have stayed at this hotel a few times before. I was quite impressed with the cleanliness of my room this time and would give 4.5 stars to the house keeping. However, the service at the hotel front desk was quite slow in general and they should do more to give priority to the loyalty club member as this is a repeated issue every time I stay at this hotel. 

When we arrived at the hotel just after midnight on Tuesday, the front desk receptionist spent some time looking at our reservation and then decided to go to the back office to get another lady (probably a more senior person?) to check us in. The next day when I woke up, I realized that she had forgotten to give me the welcome pack with welcome drink coupons as they had always done in the past. Although we might not have time to actually use the coupons this time, I was disappointed that they had not noticed their negligence until I mentioned this to them when I checked out.

Nice place. In the centre of Hong Kong ie Nathan Road. We were there for 10 days. Ate breakfast every morning there. Great dining room and food was really good. Very helpful staff. Rooms were not bad not flashy definitely will go back again soon

Location is great!  Hotel is nicely decorated and the staff was excellent.  Our room was big by HK standards and very nice.  Some areas were in need of updating such as hallway carpeting, and the exterior wall of our room was in poor condition.  All said, I'd come back to Novotel again

Arrived room wasn't ready, but got a free drink. I had a special request to be in a quiet room but right next to me a family with child!!!
Staff were very accommodating in the bar

result.adr_address: 香港油麻地彌敦道348號
result.name: 香港九龍諾富特酒店

reviews.text: 一般👌

Отель расположен в 5 минутах ходьбы от станции метро Jordan - выход B1. На главной улице Коулуна  - Nathan Road. В 7 минутах ходьбы от ночного рынка. Нас очень быстро разместили. При заселении взимается депозит 500 HKD. В номере быстрый Wi-Fi , сейф, холодильник с баром, кондиционер, телевизор, фен, чайник с принадлежностями для чая и кофе. В номере хороша шумоизоляция. Хорошие кровати. Высыпались здесь с комфортом. Понравился завтрак. Большой ассортимент продуктов. Все очень вкусно. Рекомендую всем здесь останавливаться.

result.adr_address: 香港油麻地彌敦道348號
result.name: The Square Restaurant

reviews.text: A good value for money although choices are limited for lunch. Good quality in general. Some dishes could be made better such as pork steak and shrimp. Definitely, you can find something you like. Excellent service with a clean and decent environment. Would recommend it with a limited budget.

ᴛʜᴇ sǫᴜᴀʀᴇ
早排假日同咗我嘅幾位好友去食lunch buffet，呢到嘅buffet，就算係紅日都只係要$198一位，價錢都幾經濟，咁當然，咁平嘅價錢，大家對食物種類嘅期望都要因應價錢有所調整。

海鮮有好幾款選擇，小龍蝦、 海蝦、白蜆等等都有，新鮮，好快被人拎哂，不過refill都幾快。

餐廳最近promo緊越式食物，都幾驚喜，淨係越式沙律都有成5款，牛肉沙律同魷魚沙律真係第一次試，都幾特別值得一試。

刺身我都唔知有幾多款，因為太搶手，長期都唔齊腳😆 三文魚壽司我都食咗好幾轉，雖然唔算肥美，但都新鮮好食。

熟食區嘅龍脷柳好好食，佢係蒸嘅，雖然無咗份煎香嘅味道，但由於個汁處理得唔錯，完全可以帶出魚味，要試吓。話明越式，當然唔少得食越南pho，有多款配料可選，湯底當然未去到越南嗰啲咁濃郁，但都唔錯，可以過吓口癮。

甜品賣相精美，都幾多款揀，其中檸檬撻幾好食，撻邊鬆化，檸檬味清新。最特別係呢到有即製雞蛋仔，我就去去拎埋haggen-dazs雪糕伴住嚟食。

飲品方面呢到既有罐裝飲品，又有果汁、特飲等，誠意十足。

需加一服務費，埋單4人約$870。 ⁣
裝修時尚，海鮮蟹類食品 新鮮美味 ，蘇格蘭蠔精彩絕倫，特式越南食品 富含地方特色 ，多種haagen dazs雪糕 最精彩係安格斯燒牛肉入口即溶 ，多種特色果汁及 越南式飲品包括龍眼茶珍多冰。 真係食得招積

今天星期四，來品坊食自助午餐
$158蚊一位，大家應該知道不會有驚喜
這裡環境不錯，也不趕客，我地由12點座到2點半
那裡的燒牛肉好吃
食物選擇不太多，而且熟食水準也一般。幸好生蠔好食，但略嫌細隻左少少。呢期係越南野，但係唔算太出色，越南地道小食亦唔夠多，唯一係米卷口味選擇多。飲品有檸檬茶，什果賓冶，熱情果同紅莓等等4款，選擇多。雪糕有8款哈根大師口味簡，仲要係自助任食，正。
